Prerequisites and characteristics of adult learner development. Educator's code of ethics. Personal counseling techniques: counseling, training, consulting, (business) mentoring, coaching, supervision, supervision. Customer work process and its planning. Customer target group analysis and customer work goals. Possibilities of combining methods of client work. Evaluating the effectiveness of client work and interpreting feedback.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give an overview of the main development, training and counseling techniques used in adult education and the principles of working with them.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) knows the prerequisites and characteristics of the adult learner's development; 2) knows and bases his work on the adult educator's code of ethics; 3) can analyze his own and the client's development needs; 4) chooses the appropriate development methodology according to the client's development goal; 5) knows the principles and main techniques and areas of use of training, advice, consulting, (business) mentoring and coaching; 6) plans and conducts client work sessions according to the selected development methodology or their combination; 7) is able to collect feedback on customer work and analyze and evaluate it.
